<HEAD>Head of Paris Orchestra Named Chicago Symphony Music Director</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SHERI PRASSO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sir <PERSON> Georg </PERSON> <PERSON> Solti </PERSON> is passing the baton as <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> Symphony music director to <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Barenboim </PERSON>, who an orchestra member characterized as a first-string quarterback who `` can lead us to the Super Bowl.'' The 46-year-old Argentine-born Israeli conductor and pianist was named Monday to succeed <PERSON> Solti </PERSON>, who is retiring at the end of next season after two decades as the orchestra's conductor. <PERSON> Barenboim </PERSON>, fired recently from the newly formed Opera-Bastille in a power struggle, will continue as director of the <ORGANIZATION> Paris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Orchestra </ORGANIZATION>, a position he has held for 15 years, said <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Symphony </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Dewey </PERSON>. He and <PERSON> Solti </PERSON> will work together until <PERSON> Solti </PERSON>'s retirement. `` Now we have two first-string quarterbacks, and either one can lead us to the Super Bowl,'' said timpanist <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Koss </PERSON>, chairman of the Orchestra Members' Committee. `` We've played for maestro <PERSON> Barenboim </PERSON> many times and know he is truly a world-class conductor, absolutely first-rate.'' `` In choosing <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Barenboim </PERSON>, I'm completely confident that we have made the best possible choice for our orchestra,'' <ORGANIZATION> Orchestral </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said. `` With his infectious enthusiasm, his commitment to excellence and his exceptional credentials, I have no doubt that he will build on his previous accomplishments as well as those of the orchestra.'' The 76-year-old Hungarian-born <PERSON> Solti </PERSON>, who has won a record-high 26 <ORGANIZATION> Grammys </ORGANIZ