<HEAD>Track Athletes Kill Six, Wound One In Fujian</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two track-and-field athletes using starter pistols killed six people and wounded another for unknown reasons before police killed one of them in a shootout, a newspaper reported today. The official <ORGANIZATION> China </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sports </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> said 300 armed police officers surrounded a building in the sports center in the southern city of <LOCATION> Fuzhou </LOCATION> on Monday and exchanged shots with <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> <PERSON> Weidong </PERSON>, a 110-meter hurdler, and <PERSON> Li </PERSON> <PERSON> Zhichuan </PERSON>, who specializes in the decathlon. <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> died in the shootout and <PERSON> Li </PERSON> was wounded, the newspaper said. The incident began Sunday morning when <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> and <PERSON> Li </PERSON> met three acquaintances and asked them for $ 540. The report said it was not clear why the two men asked for the money, but their request was refused. An official at the <LOCATION> Fuzhou </LOCATION> city police department said `` women were involved in the incident'' but declined to elaborate. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> has recently seen a rise in prostitution, especially in the richer cities along the country's coast. The pair went to the room of their three acquaintances later that afternoon, crashed through the door and began firing, killing the three acquaintances, the paper said. The pair then locked themselves in the room. A short while later, two men and two women entered. <PERSON> Li </PERSON> and <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> killed three of them and seriously wounded the woman, the paper said. They then fled to the provincial sports center, where several close friends, also track-and-field athletes, helped them hide. Early Monday morning, police found <PERSON> Li </PERSON> and <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> hiding in the attic of the five-story building. After a stand-off of almost three hours, police killed <PERSON> Shang </PERSON> and captured <P