<TEXT>
 A judge sentenced a woman to 3 -LCB- to nine years in prison for plotting to murder her estranged husband and using her teen-age son to hire someone to do the job. <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyle-Lawton </PERSON>, a 39-year-old mother of three, pleaded guilty last September to charges of solicitation to commit murder and corruption of minors. <LOCATION> Montgomery </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Judge <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Yohn </PERSON> on Monday ordered her jailed in the state prison at <LOCATION> Muncy </LOCATION>. Assistant District Attorney <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> McNulty </PERSON> presented testimony at the two-day sentencing hearing that Ms. <PERSON> Boyle-Lawton </PERSON> a year ago told her son <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyle </PERSON>, then 17, that she needed his help to kill her husband, <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Lawton </PERSON>, to `` get him out of her hair'' and collect on his $ 300,000 insurance policy. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyle </PERSON> found a `` hired killer'' in a classmate at <ORGANIZATION> Wissahickon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> near <LOCATION> Ambler </LOCATION>, who was actually a state trooper posing as a student while investigating drug trafficking at the school, officials said. Trooper <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Fulton </PERSON> testified that he met with Ms. <PERSON> Boyle-Lawton </PERSON> several times to plan the killing and that she gave him money for a gun and silencer. She provided him with a $ 1,000 down payment, pictures of her husband and a written description of him, <PERSON> Fulton </PERSON> said. The trooper secretly wore electronic equipment to record their conversations. Portions of the wiretap were played back in the courtroom, including Ms. <PERSON> Boyle-Lawton </PERSON>'s voice stating amid obscenities, `` I want him dead. I want the insurance.'' Ms. <