<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man accused of faking his own death in a $ 1.5 million insurance fraud was arrested carrying the driver's license of the man whose body was part of the scam, an <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> agent said <PERSON> Melvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON>, co-founder of Just Sweats, a <ORGANIZATION> Whitehall </ORGANIZATION>, Ohio-based athletic clothing store chain, was arrested in connection with the insurance scam at <LOCATION> Dallas-Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> Sunday night by <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> agents, police said Monday. The suspect was carrying a driver's license and other papers that belonged to <PERSON> Ellis </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Greene </PERSON>, a former <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> man whose body was found in a <LOCATION> Glendale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, doctor's office and reported to be that of <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON>, said <PERSON> Douglass </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ogden </PERSON>, agent in charge of the <ORGANIZATION> Columbus </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> office. The body later was identified as that of <PERSON> Greene </PERSON>. But the arrested man denied he was <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON> and plans to fight extradition to <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Ogden </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON>, 47, and his business partner, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON>, 25, have been sought by police in <LOCATION> Columbus </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> since mid-1988, when it was discovered that <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON> was not dead and <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> had disappeared. Theft charges against <PERSON> Hanson </PERSON> and <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> were filed Oct. 14 by <ORGANIZATION> Farmers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION