blindness to the consequences of that policy. Meanwhile, Sen. <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Texas </LOCATION>, introduced legislation designed to save faltering rural hospitals by boosting government reimbursements for patient care and improving physican recruitment. <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> blamed inequities in the <ORGANIZATION> Medicare </ORGANIZATION> prospective payment system for contributing to the problems of rural hospitals. Under the program, hospitals are reimbursed for the average costs of their elderly Medicare patients and not on actual costs.
