 <ORGANIZATION> Yugo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the troubled importer of inexpensive Yugoslavian-made cars, its parent company and a sister corporation have filed for protection from creditors under federal bankruptcy laws. Sagging sales and the loss of dealerships were among the problems cited by <LOCATION> Yugo </LOCATION> in November when company President <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Prior </PERSON> resigned. <ORGANIZATION> Yugo </ORGANIZATION>, its parent <ORGANIZATION> Global </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, and a separate affiliate, <ORGANIZATION> Proton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said Monday about 300 companies and individuals may hold claims against them.
