<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A commission including three former presidents has proposed a national health care system that would ensure access to basic medical services for all Americans with financing by all but the poorest. The system is designed to extend health care to the estimated 37 million uninsured Americans, curtail soaring health costs and improve medical care nationwide, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Leadership </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> on </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Care </ORGANIZATION> said Monday.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
