<HEAD>Yugo Dealers Learn of Company's Bankruptcy</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Yuto Bankruptcy, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By FREDERICK STANDISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Terry </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanks </PERSON> has about 30 Yugos on the lot of <ORGANIZATION> Sundance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chevrolet </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Lansing </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, and he's wondering what's going to happen to them <ORGANIZATION> Yugo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the troubled importer of inexpensive Yugoslavian-made cars, its parent company and an affiliate on Monday filed for protection under federal bankruptcy laws. <LOCATION> Yugo </LOCATION> officials maintain they want to continue doing business in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and that another marketing system would be set up. The company said the supply of cars, which sell for about $ 5,000 apiece, would continue along with warranty work. That was good news for dealers like <PERSON> Hanks </PERSON>, many of whom tried to talk the company out of filing the bankruptcy papers. `` It's a good little car,'' <PERSON> Hanks </PERSON> said, calling the bankruptcy filing a `` shame.'' <PERSON> Hanks </PERSON> said in a telephone interview that his dealership sells about 400 cars a month, 30 of which are Yugos. But he also said it was possible the dealership would get rid of the franchise if <ORGANIZATION> Yugo </ORGANIZATION>'s price rose too much. <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Hill </PERSON>, sales manager of <PERSON> Elhart </PERSON> <PERSON> Dodge-Yugo </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Holland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, agreed that the boxy, economy car is a good seller. `` The <LOCATION> Yugo </LOCATION> has done a good job for us,'' he said. `` It's filled a good -LRB- car market -RRB- niche.'' He said the <LOCATION> Yugo </LOCATION> has outsold every model Dodge offers except its popular Caravan minivan. Nationwide, Yugo sales dropped 35 percent in 1988 compared with 1987. <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Mackie </PERSON>,