<HEAD>USX Reports Fourth-Quarter Turnaround</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday reported profits of $ 158 million in the fourth quarter of 1988, saying a rejuvenated steel division helped it rebound from a $ 14 million loss in the same period a year earlier. The nation's largest steelmaker said the profit, equal to 55 cents a share, came on sales of $ 4.4 billion, up from $ 4.3 billion in the last three months of 1987. <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Roderick </PERSON> attributed the turnaround in part to the company's improved steel division, USS. Operating income there was $ 501 million on sales of $ 5.8 billion, four times higher than the $ 125 million on sales of $ 3.7 billion reported for 1987. <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION>, formerly known as <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>, also is the parent of <ORGANIZATION> Marathon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Gas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. For the entire year, <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> said earnings tripled to $ 756 million, or $ 2.62 a share, on sales of $ 16.9 billion That compares to profits of $ 219 million, or 54 cents a share, on sales of $ 14.9 billion in 1987. `` All of our major segments were profitable in 1988, and we expect improved profitability in both our steel and energy segments in 1989,'' <PERSON> Roderick </PERSON> said in a statement. `` We are stronger financially now than in any recent year.'' Operating income from energy operations rose 7 percent, to $ 475 million from $ 444 million in 1987, despite continued trouble at <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Gas. The unit reported losses of $ 31 million for 1988 and $ 7 million for the fourth quarter, compared with operating income of $ 2 million for 1987 and a loss of $ 4 million for the 1987 fourth quarter. <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> blamed diminished margins on gas gathering and weak crude oil prices for the <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Gas losses.
