ffering of <ORGANIZATION> BP </ORGANIZATION> shares in October 1987. The sale by the Conservative government under its policy of privatization coincided with the stock market crash. The offering, which included the government's remaining 31.5 percent stake in <ORGANIZATION> BP </ORGANIZATION>, was seriously undersubscribed. Although the price <ORGANIZATION> BP </ORGANIZATION> will pay the Kuwaitis amounts to 305 pence for each of the 790 million shares owned by <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> BP </ORGANIZATION> will effectively pay 247 pence a share because of tax credits. <PERSON> Walters </PERSON> said the repurchase would be completed by mid-March.
