<FIRST>r f AM-Norway-Jobless     01-31 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Norway-Jobless,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Norway's Unemployment Nearly Doubles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The number of unemployed Norwegians nearly doubled in one year to a postwar record with 4 percent out of work, the government announced Tuesday. `` The registered unemployment rate increased to an extraordinary level -LRB- in January -RRB-, and the figures are the highest that have been registered in postwar time,'' the government labor agency said. Officials at <ORGANIZATION> Norges </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, the central bank, had predicted the increase, calling it a `` necessary evil'' in an austerity program aimed at reducing inflation and other economic problems. The official January figures of 86,600 jobless did not include 36,700 people involved in government-funded work programs. <LOCATION> Norway </LOCATION> went into a sharp economic decline in the mid-1980s with the drop in prices of oil, a major export. The last unemployment record was in January 1985, when 79,700 people were officially listed as jobless. The labor agency said the January figure was up 16,900 from last month and up 44,000 from a year earlier.
</TEXT>
