<HEAD>NADA President Issues Challenges to Automakers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By FREDERICK STANDISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Automakers are discriminating against the nation's automobile dealers, who must unite to make buying and selling cars a fairer game in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, the president of a dealers' group said Tuesday. `` We dealers are swivel-necked from turning the other cheek, and it simply has to stop,'' said <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Tonkin </PERSON>, the 1989 president of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Automobile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dealers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. `` We want automakers to be healthy and profitable, but not by wreaking havoc on the best, most loyal friends they ever had, their dealers,'' said <LOCATION> Tonkin </LOCATION>, a dealer with 10 stores holding 14 automobile franchises in the <LOCATION> Portland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ore. </LOCATION>, area. In his speech to about 20,000 peopel attending <ORGANIZATION> NADA </ORGANIZATION>'s annual convention, <LOCATION> Tonkin </LOCATION> singled out the subsidies from automakers to companies that buy fleets of cars. He said he wanted the makers to `` simply tell us ` We will sell to no one for less than we sell to our franchised dealers.''' But company officials for the Big Three automakers said their fleet brokers are franchised dealers. C.N. <PERSON> Moore </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>' vice president for customer sales and service, said from his office in <LOCATION> Detroit </LOCATION> that all <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>'s fleet sales are through franchised dealers, except for sales to the federal government `` These people that <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Tonkin </PERSON> was talking to today are the people who deliver all these cars to fleet customers,'' <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORG