<HEAD>Earnings Rise in Double Digits at Warner-Lambert, Schering-Plough</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Schering-Plough </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its fourth-quarter earnings rose 24 percent and attributed the rise to strong performances in international sales. Another big drug and consumer products company, <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, also cited sales gains in reporting its earnings for the same period jumped 17 percent. <ORGANIZATION> Schering-Plough </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Madison </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, said it earned $ 92.9 million, or 83 cents per share, in the final quarter of 1988, up from $ 75.2 million, or 67 cents per share, in the same period a year earlier. Sales for the fourth quarter totaled $ 739.9 million, a 12 percent rise over $ 663.5 million the year before. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Luciano </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer, said international sales turned in an `` exceptional'' performance during the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION>, headquartered in <LOCATION> Morris </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Plains </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, said it earned $ 77.5 million, or $ 1.14 per share, in the fourth quarter, up from $ 66.3 million, or 95 cents per share, in the same period of 1987. Sales increased 11 percent to $ 997.9 million from $ 899 million. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION>'s chairman and chief executive officer, attributed the performance to strong sales in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and abroad. For all of 1988, <ORGANIZATION> Schering-Plough </ORGANIZATION> reported earnings of $ 389.8 million, or $ 3.48 per share, up 23.2 percent from $ 316.4 million, or $ 2.73 per share, during 1987. Sales in 1988 were $ 2.97 billion, a 10 percent rise over the $ 2.7 billion reported in 1987. <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION> said it earned $ 340.3 million, or $ 5 per share, during 1988, up 15 percent from $ 295.8 million, or $ 4.15 per share, in 1987. Sales increased 14 percent to $ 3.91 billion from $ 3.44 billion.
